challengeName: NASA SMG Import and Export Functionality
detailedRequirements:
Task Overview

NASA need to develop a software version of the Solution Mechanism Guide so that users can navigate a search form to a filtered subset of solution mechanisms that are a best fit for their specific needs based on the criteria they input (experience similar to finding a car rental or airline ticket online but more fun and NASA-y).

Task Requirements

You will build an import/export functionality and integrate it in the SMG admin frontend :

  • Add new tab to "manage help"  page :
    • Tab name is "Import/Export SMG"
    • The csv file format :
      • Each file contains exactly one SMG entity.
      • Each row is corresponded to SMG characterstics
        • If charecterstic is lookup/multi-value then values should be comma separated IDs (not the string value)
    • The screenshot above is how the final page should look like
      • buttons to export and get csv template
      • It should have a single file browse field with ability to add more file input files.
    • When user select files, then click "import", the import functionality will start by uploading files then inserting them one by one into DB.
      • Errors during import should be returned back to user, the error should be very clear, it should details what file is the cause, what line and what characterstic. and cause of error.
      • If one of the imported file fails, all successful imported files should be reverted so a *transaction* is important in this feature.
    • For exporting functional will read all SMG entries, create a csv file for each SMG and group them in zip file and send the zip file to user for download.
    • Files will be in csv format, each row represents a characterstic, it contains comma separated values  (if the characterstics is text field, then it will contain exactly one value)
    •  "download template" is to help user to underestand how to create csv file for importing or to understand the structure of exported csv :
      • it will be a zip file stored in application directory, this functionality won't have any db interaction.
      • the location of zip file should be configured.
      • you can create a sample zip file and include it in your submission as demonstration. the real zip file content will be created by Copilot.
  • update README to explain how to import/export, and include sample snapshot of csfv file for import/export.

Testing

In order to make sure that the right tool is built, we are providing you with the exact list of characterstics, their types and possible values (if it is lookup). and we are providing you with excel sheet contains mutiple SMG sheets. You need to create csv file for each SMG and include it in your submission. also make sure to test your submission (import/export) before submitting to make sure you built it right.
